            <div>
             <div class="panel-pane">
              <h2 class="title">
               Introduction
              </h2>
              <div class="content">
               <div class="node node-type-page" id="node-82">
                <div class="node-inner">
                 <div class="content">
                  <p>
                   This website contains valuable information to help students, faculty, and staff understand some of the policies and regulations of the University.  Policies on this website pertain to campus safety (including harassment and discrimination), the confidentiality of student records, drug and alcohol use, student leaves, and political activity, as well as others.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   <strong>
                    Who Is Governed by These Policies?
                   </strong>
                   All students, faculty, staff, affiliates, and visitors to Columbia University.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   <strong>
                    Who Should Know These Policies?
                   </strong>
                   All students, faculty, staff, affiliates, and visitors to the University.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   This is a useful reference to several important policies Columbia University maintains, but it is not exhaustive.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   This policy online reference is intended to provide information for the guidance of the Columbia community. The editors have exercised their best efforts to ensure the accuracy of the information contained herein, but accuracy cannot be absolutely guaranteed. If you have any questions regarding these policies, please contact:
                   <a href="mailto:essential-policies@columbia.edu">
                    essential-policies@columbia.edu
                   </a>
                   .
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   Information presented here is subject to change, and the University reserves the right to depart without notice from any policy or procedure referred to in this online reference. These
                   <em>
                    Essential Policies
                   </em>
                   are not intended to and should not be regarded as a contract between the University and any student or other person.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   Produced by:
                   <br/>
                   Columbia University
                   <br/>
                   Butler Hall
                   <br/>
                   400 West 119th Street
                   <br/>
                   New York, NY 10027
                   <br/>
                   <a href="mailto:essential-policies@columbia.edu">
                    essential-policies@columbia.edu
                   </a>
                   <br/>
                   <a href="https://www.essential-policies.columbia.edu" title="https://www.essential-policies.columbia.edu">
                    https://www.essential-policies.columbia.edu
                   </a>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   <br/>
                   <em>
                    Copyright © 2016 The Trustees of Columbia University in the City of New York
                   </em>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
               <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
              </div>
             </div>
             <div class="panel-separator">
             </div>
             <div class="panel-pane">
              <h2 class="title">
               About this site
              </h2>
              <div class="content">
               <div class="node node-type-page" id="node-99">
                <div class="node-inner">
                 <div class="content">
                  This website is intended only to provide information for the guidance of the Columbia community. Accuracy of content cannot be absolutely guaranteed. Anyone who needs to rely on any particular policy is advised to verify it independently. Information presented here is subject to change, and the University reserves the right to depart without notice from any policy or procedure referred to on this website. The policies on this website should not be regarded as a contract between the University and any student or other person.
                  <p>
                   Should you have any questions or comments about
                   <em>
                    Essential Policies
                   </em>
                   or about the site in general, please
                   <a href="mailto:essential-policies@columbia.edu" target="_blank">
                    contact us
                   </a>
                   .
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
